# Commit And Push Completed Work

- After completing and verifying a user-requested code change, commit the intended changes and push the current branch to its configured remote.
- Include the rule file itself when it has changed.
- Never discard, overwrite, or silently include unrelated user changes.
- Do not push known broken or incomplete work; report any verification or Git blocker clearly.
- Report the branch and short commit hash after a successful push.
